Two people have been injured after a taxi was T-boned by a bakkie on Botha Avenue in Centurion on Wednesday.According to reports the bakkie was traveling at high speed when it hit the taxi.Emer-G-Med&#8217;s spokesperson Max Cohen said, &#8220;Two patients sustained moderate injuries, with one requiring Advanced Life Support intervention.&#8220;They were treated at the scene before being transported to Netcare Unitas Hospital for further treatment&#8221;&#8220;Local authorities were on the scene to investigate exact events leading up to the collision,&#8221; Cohen said.-TNA Reporter